The Great Pyramid is three institutions in one structure: public kingship machine, hidden soul-adjudication system, and sealed cosmic containment vessel.

Six construction eras: processional causeways and lion gates; priestly archives and embalmer kilns; catacomb sublevels for mass interment and corpse-labor; Jackal Tribunal weighing halls; militarized upper sancta; reverse-solar geometry sealing the Black Sun Shard at the apex.

The Shard is a fragment of anti-light that consumes names, certainties, and memory.
Pharaoh Ramesses accepted partial soul-binding to keep the Shard dormant.

The Solar Court of the Undivided Disk splintered into five offices: Dawn Liturgists, Ledger Priests, Embalmer Houses, Jackal Tribunal, and Seal College.
Their rivalries define the pyramid's modern hauntings.
Ushabti guardians still patrol processional routes. The Tribunal's masked judges still deliver verdicts.

The pyramid sealed itself when its civilization collapsed, automatic protocols engaging without living custodians.
Tomb extraction crews and cult revivals have since reopened lower courts.
Old factional ghosts defend particular eras and forged histories.
